brief in declensions
In Pāḷi Language，nouns can be change into eight different cases as below：
[[nom]]inative case，for more details can see [[form of nom.]]
[[inst]]rumental case，for more details can see [[form of inst.]]
[[acc]]usative case，for more details can see [[form of acc.]]
[[dat]]ive case，for more details can see [[form of dat.]]
[[abl]]ative case，for more details can see [[form of abl.]]
[[gen]]itive case，for more details can see [[form of gen.]]
[[loc]]ative case，for more details can see [[form of loc.]]
[[voc]]ative case，for more details can see [[form of voc.]]

brief in declensions

[[aor]]ist，for more details can see [[form of pres.]]
[[cond]]itional，for more details can see [[form of aor.]]
[[fut]]ure，for more details can see [[form of fut.]]
[[imp]]erative，for more details can see [[form of imp.]]
[[opt]]ative，for more details can see [[form of opt.]]
[[pres]]ent，for more details can see [[form of cond.]]
